<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="918" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d918">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2751.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Consul at Juárez</gloss>. </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-10">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 10, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department approves your proposed action, as stated in your telegram
                            February 7, concerning protest to anti-Maderists now in power at Casas
                            Grandes against taking firearms from Americans. You should make your
                            protest emphatic, and base it on the ground that Americans must not be
                            left without means of defense to protect themselves during the present
                            unsettled conditions against marauding robbers.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>